<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-275-188  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 275 188.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  March 26 1990 n293 p40(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Document argues for Bell freedom. (white paper seeks federallifting of restrictions on manufacturing by regional Bells)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Killette, Kathleen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Regional Bell operating companies (RBOCs) are circulating anuncredited white paper on Capitol Hill that calls for liftingmanufacturing restrictions opposed on them by the AT and Tdivestiture agreement.andP;  The House Telecommunications Subcommitteeis weighing legislation that would lift the restrictions.andP;  Thewhite paper attacks AT and T's contentions that lifting therestrictions would hurt US employment and could presage the RBOCsforming ties with foreign manufacturers.andP;  The white paper turnsthose contentions on their head, contending that post-divestitureAT and T has cut 60,000 manufacturing jobs and moved manufacturingactivities overseas while maintaining flat investment in researchand development..andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     LobbyingBell Regional Holding CompaniesUnited States. CongressDeregulationForeign InvestmentCommunications IndustryEmployment.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Ammunition against manufacturing ban. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>